    <name>Bottles</name>
    <summary>Easily run Windows software on Linux with üç∑ Bottles!</summary>
    <developer_name>Mirko Brombin</developer_name>
    <description>
        <p>Easily run Windows software on Linux with üç∑ Bottles!</p>
        <p>Bottles is a modern tool that refines and simplifies running Windows software on Linux!</p>
        <p>Our built-in dependency installation system allows for easy access to a broad level of software
            compatibility. We also include a download manager for downloading the official components:
            runner (wine, proton), dxvk, dependencies, etc.</p>
        <p>Features such as bottle versioning allow you to keep your work safe and restore it later!</p>
        <p>Features:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Create your bottles using preconfigured environments or create your own</li>
          <li>Run every executable (.exe/.msi) in your bottles, directly from the context menu form your file manager</li>
          <li>Automated detection of applications installed in your bottles</li>
          <li>Add environment variables easily</li>
          <li>Override DLLs directly from bottle preferences</li>
          <li>On-the-fly runner change for any Bottle</li>
          <li>Various optimizations for better gaming performance (esync, fsync, dxvk, cache, shader compiler, offload .. and much more.)</li>
          <li>Automatic installation and management of Wine and Proton runners</li>
          <li>Automatic bottle repair in case of breakage</li>
          <li>Integrated Dependencies installer based on a community-driver repository</li>
          <li>Integrated Task manager for wine processes</li>
          <li>Easy access to ProtonDB and WineHQ for support</li>
          <li>Configurations update system across Bottles versions</li>
          <li>Bottles backup and import</li>
          <li>Easily import wineprefix from other managers</li>
          <li>Bottles versioning (experimental)</li>
          <li>.. and much more that you can find by installing Bottles!</li>
        </ul>
    </description>
